    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aryballoi having the early rounded form characteristic of Early Protocorinthian art. It was originally derived from the globe-shaped wine jars, oinochoe, of the 9th century BCE Geometric period.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050844/Protocorinthian Geometric Aryballos (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具有早期原科林斯藝術風格的早期圓形特徵小圓壺。此種圓壺最早源自球狀酒壺－長柄陶壺（oinochoe），出現於西元前九世紀的「幾何時期」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aryballoi die de vroege ronde vorm hadden die karakteristiek was voor vroeg-proto-Korinthische kunst. Ze waren oorspronkelijk afgeleid van de bolvormige wijnkruiken, oinochoe, uit de geometrische periode in de 9de eeuw v. Chr.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000119919/RKD-Nederlands Instituut voor Kunstgeschiedenis [database] (2021-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
